PREAMBLE

PhishGuard is an advanced, AI-powered email security platform designed to protect 
organizations from sophisticated phishing attacks, malware, and email-based threats. 
This license governs the use, modification, and distribution of the PhishGuard 
software and associated documentation.

The PhishGuard Enterprise License (PEL) is specifically crafted for cybersecurity 
software to balance the benefits of open-source collaboration with the need to 
protect intellectual property and maintain the integrity of security solutions 
used by enterprises worldwide.

DEFINITIONS

"Software" refers to the PhishGuard platform, including but not limited to source 
code, object code, documentation, configuration files, AI models, threat detection 
algorithms, and any associated materials.

"Licensor" refers to Chukwuebuka Tobiloba Nwaizugbe, the copyright holder and 
creator of the Software.

"You" or "Your" refers to any individual or entity exercising permissions under 
this License.

"Internal Use" means use of the Software within an organization for its own 
business operations, research, development, or security purposes, without 
redistribution or commercial exploitation of the Software itself.

"Commercial Redistribution" means distributing, selling, licensing, or otherwise 
making the Software available to third parties as part of a commercial product 
or service offering.

"Modified Work" means any work based on the Software, including but not limited 
to derivative works, adaptations, or works containing the Software or portions 
thereof.

